.TH UPGRADE-ARCH 1 "December 2025" "distup 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
upgrade-arch \- upgrade Arch Linux rolling release
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B upgrade-arch
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B upgrade-arch
performs system upgrades on Arch Linux. Supports standard upgrades,
keyring refresh, and cache cleanup operations.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be done without making any changes.
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-V
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Show help message.
.SH INTERACTIVE MENU
.TP
.B 1) Standard upgrade
Sync databases and upgrade all packages.
.TP
.B 2) Refresh + Upgrade
Refresh keyring, sync databases, and upgrade.
.TP
.B 3) Upgrade + Clean
Upgrade packages and clean package cache.
.TP
.B 4) Full maintenance
Refresh keyring, upgrade, and clean cache.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/log/upgrade-arch-*.log
Log file containing detailed upgrade output.
.TP
.I /etc/pacman.conf
Pacman configuration (backed up before operations).
